OL,6,FWomen's health
OL,8,FWhile discussing women's health, the
OL,9,Fminister and his team were questioned
OL,10,Fon contraception, IVF treatment and
OL,11,Fthe termination of pregnancies.
OL,13,FThe panel learned that work on most
OL,14,Fchanges to abortion law has been
OL,15,Fdelayed until after the next island
OL,16,Felection in 2026 due to insufficient
OL,17,Fresources.
